news.title: Ahmedabad development body doubles fees for plan documents
news.para: Fees for measurement sheets also doubled, from Rs 500 to Rs 1,000. Final plot F forms now cost Rs 500 (up from Rs 300), and zoning certificates are Rs 500 (up from Rs 300).

news.title: Kolkata: NKDA hosts property tax assistance camp in New Town
news.para: The camp will continue till March 31 on the ground floor of the NKDA administrative building in Action Area ID.

news.title: Jaipur development body starts work to develop Rajasthan’s first land pooling scheme
news.para: Officials said that this scheme was made keeping in mind the interests of farmers or landholders, in which for the first time a provision was made to give 45% land to farmers or landholders in exchange for acquisition.

news.title: NGT asks Ludhiana civic body chief to explain non-compliance with orders on illegal structures
news.para: The NGT, in its final orders on July 4, 2024, directed the MC to remove the illegal structures and encroachments from green belts situated in Sarabha Nagar and Model Town Extension in two months.

news.title: CMRL allocates Rs 154 crore for acquiring land for metro rail project in Coimbatore
news.para: The city corporation will soon carry out a land plan survey for the land acquisition with the help of CMRL officials, while the revenue department officials will carry out the land acquisition work.

news.title: Apartments completed before Feb 25, 2017 are eligible for registration: Odisha government
news.para: In a notification released on Saturday, the department confirmed that apartments completed before Feb 25, 2017, remain eligible for registration under the current Act.

news.title: Former Himachal Pradesh RERA chief faces graft allegations over misuse of funds
news.para: The complainant has also sought the registration of an FIR against Baldi under Section 13(1) and (2) of the Prevention of Corruption Act.

news.title: Mumbai: Developers pay regularisation charges after BMC issues stop work notice
news.para: The notice issued to YM Systems by BMC E-ward, issued on January 7, said the developer was carrying out work without valid permission, beyond part 20th floor up to 23rd floor.

news.title: Budget 2025: National guidance framework for global capability centres announced
news.para: Real estate experts expects the introduction of a national guidance framework for global capability centres to boost the commercial real estate sector in tier-II and tier-III cities as well.

news.title: Budget 2025 will improve quality of life in urban areas: Housing Minister
news.para: Khattar stated that the Budget 2025-26 lays a strong foundation for Viksit Bharat by driving transformative reforms in urban development, housing, and infrastructure.

news.title: WeWork India Management files IPO papers with Sebi
news.para: The Embassy Group-promoted firm's IPO is entirely an Offer for Sale (OFS) of equity shares of up to 4.37 crore equity shares, according to the draft red herring prospectus (DRHP) filed on Friday.

news.title: CGST law amendment may hit real estate sector: Experts
news.para: ​Against the backdrop of a Supreme Court ruling related to input tax credit, the government has mooted substituting the word 'plant or machinery' with 'plant and machinery' under a section of the Central Goods and Services Tax (CGST) Act.

news.title: Government hikes threshold for TDS on rent to Rs 6 lakh
news.para: This will reduce the number of transactions liable to TDS, thus benefitting small taxpayers receiving small payments, the finance minister added.

news.title: China home sales decline again as stimulus wanes
news.para: Beijing is struggling to revive the property market amid weak domestic demand and a worsening job situation. While the housing sector has picked up modestly on the back of government support, improvements have mostly been in the second-hand market, with buyers worried about developers' ability to finish projects on time.

news.title: Kolkata civic body begins demolition of illegal building on Christopher Road
news.para: Mayor Firhad Hakim said while he empathised with the flat owners, the building would have to go as it was unauthorised. But, he said, if the owners approached the KMC and applied for the state scheme for the homeless, the civic body would try to facilitate the construction of ‘Banglar Bari' for them.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC writes to MMRDA about Rs 550 crore property tax dues of contractor
news.para: The BMC joint municipal commissioner of the assessment and collection department, it was pointed out that despite multiple follow-ups, J Kumar Infraprojects cited a clause in its agreement stating that MMRDA is responsible for property tax payment.

news.title: Jaipur: JMC-G to hold camps for 100% collection of urban development tax
news.para: JMC-G commissioner Rukmani Riar instructed all zone deputy commissioners, revenue officers and revenue inspectors of the civic body to achieve 100% target in collection of revenues.

news.title: Real Estate Budget 2025: Government allows benefits on two self-occupied properties
news.para: Now tax payers can claim nil valuation for two self-occupied properties, compared to just one earlier. This move eliminates the tax burden on notional rental income from a second home.

news.title: Budget 2025: Urban challenge fund of Rs one lakh crore announced to drive infrastructure growth
news.para: With Rs 10,000 crore earmarked for 2025-26, the Urban challenge fund is set to address land and development challenges, promote social infrastructure, and facilitate the expansion of smart cities and urban corridors.

news.title: Real Estate Budget 2025: SWAMIH Fund 2.0 announced to revive stalled housing projects
news.para: SWAMIH initiative has already completed 50,000 homes, with another 40,000 expected to be handed over by 2025, FM said. The newly launched SWAMIH fund 2.0 is expected to facilitate the completion of an additional one lakh housing units.
